		<title>Golden Sugar Company Gets Recognition For Safety Standards, Wins Global Food Safety Initiative Award 2019</title>
		<link>https://fmnplc.com/golden-sugar-company-gets-recognition-safety-standards-wins-global-food-safety-initiative-award-2019/</link>
				<pubDate>Wed, 13 Mar 2019 09:02:38 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Flour Mills Nigeria]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Press]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://fmnplc.com/?p=2312</guid>
				<description><![CDATA[<p>Flour Mills of Nigeria Plc. (referred to as “Flour Mills” or “FMN”), Nigeria’s leading Foods and Agro-allied Group, today announced that one of its subsidiaries and a major advocate for the development of the Sugar Value Chain in Nigeria, Golden Sugar Company Limited, has won The Global Food Safety Initiative (GFSI) Awards in Nice, France. [&#8230;]</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://fmnplc.com/golden-sugar-company-gets-recognition-safety-standards-wins-global-food-safety-initiative-award-2019/">Golden Sugar Company Gets Recognition For Safety Standards, Wins Global Food Safety Initiative Award 2019</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://fmnplc.com">FMN</a>.</p>
]]></description>
								<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Flour Mills of Nigeria Plc. (referred to as “Flour Mills” or “FMN”), Nigeria’s leading Foods and Agro-allied Group, today announced that one of its subsidiaries and a major advocate for the development of the Sugar Value Chain in Nigeria, Golden Sugar Company Limited, has won The Global Food Safety Initiative (GFSI) Awards in Nice, France.</p>
<p>The award was announced during this year’s GFSI conference in Nice, which brings industry leaders together to discuss the key food safety trends in the FMCG sector. The Awards intend to reflect the diversity of the GFSI Global Markets Programme around the world today from Africa, Asia, the Americas and Europe.</p>
<p>Mike Robach, Chairman of the GFSI Board said: “The Global Markets Awards 2019 recognizes the commitment of companies all over the world to their food safety journey. This year, the Selection Committee focused on the effort and innovations the companies have made in creating an environment for food safety and a culture of continuous improvement.</p>
<p>Golden Sugar Company, which by the way was the only recipient company from Africa this year was recognized for boosting its client base beyond direct consumers to multinational industrial clients and reduced food safety-related complaints. <a href="https://fmnplc.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Golden-Sugar-Company-Is-Recognized-for-Food-Safety-Wins-Global-Food-Safety-Initiative-Award-2019-003.pdf">Read More</a></p>
