								<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>As part of activities to commemorate this year’s International Women’s Day, with the theme, Balance for better, FMN recently unveiled its Women’s Network, aptly named, “The Amazons.”<br />
The unveiling was performed by John Coumantaros, Chairman, FMN, in company of the GMD, Paul Gbededo, and the Head of HR, Kemi Aro at an event held in Apapa recently.</p>
<p>It was disclosed that the Women’s Network which was designed to identify and groom the next generation of women leaders in FMN will be spearheaded by, Mrs Salamatu Hussaini, a member of the FMN board.</p>
<p>Speaking at the event, John Coumantaros said: “The mentorship program will arm our women with the necessary tools and inspiration to rise to better opportunities, break the glass ceilings and take on the world.”</p>
<p>Other highlight of the events included a panel discussion session, where the women shared experiences on career progressions, work-life balance and how to succeed in a male dominated corporate world. Some the panelist included, Hansatu Adegbite, Executive Director of Women in Management, Business and Public Service (WIMBIZ) in Lagos, Yewande Sadiku, Execitive secretary/CEO, Nigerian Investment Promotion Commission, Mrs. Marie Owoniyi, Experienced banker, and HR professional and Arinola Lydia Aruleba, Head of Sugar Value Chain, in Golden Sugar Limited, a subsidiary of the FMN</p>
