		<title>Bank Of Industry Boss Visits Sorghum Mill At Northern Nigeria Flour Mills In Kano</title>
		<link>https://fmnplc.com/bank-industry-boss-visits-sorghum-mill-northern-nigeria-flour-mills-kano/</link>
				<comments>https://fmnplc.com/bank-industry-boss-visits-sorghum-mill-northern-nigeria-flour-mills-kano/#comments</comments>
				<pubDate>Tue, 03 Oct 2017 20:57:17 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[General]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Press]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://fmnplc.com/?p=1652</guid>
				<description><![CDATA[<p>The Managing Director and Chief Executive Officer of the Bank of Industry, Mr Olukayode Pitan, recently paid a courtesy call to the Northern Nigerian Flour Mills in Kano. He was accompanied by a team of senior officials from the Bank: Ibrahim Bisallah, Northwest Regional Manager; Omar Shekarau, SME North General Manager; Joseph Babatunde, General Manager, [&#8230;]</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://fmnplc.com/bank-industry-boss-visits-sorghum-mill-northern-nigeria-flour-mills-kano/">Bank Of Industry Boss Visits Sorghum Mill At Northern Nigeria Flour Mills In Kano</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://fmnplc.com">FMN</a>.</p>
]]></description>
								<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>The Managing Director and Chief Executive Officer of the Bank of Industry, Mr Olukayode Pitan, recently paid a courtesy call to the Northern Nigerian Flour Mills in Kano.</p>
<p>He was accompanied by a team of senior officials from the Bank: Ibrahim Bisallah, Northwest Regional Manager; Omar Shekarau, SME North General Manager; Joseph Babatunde, General Manager, Large Enterprises and Lolo Kadafa, Group Head of the Food Processing Unit.</p>
<p>The team was received by Charl Marais, the Managing Director, NNFM and Alhaji Sani Umar, the Executive Consultant of the company, and were taken on a tour of the facilities at the mill.</p>
<p>The Sorghum mill which is part of a strategic investment drive in Kano, by Flour Mills of Nigeria Plc, was built at a cost of about N2 billion, has a capacity of 100, 000 metric tons per annum and will help advance the Group’s drive towards establishing an ambitious Pan-Nigerian network of grains aggregation and distribution centers.</p>
<p>Mr Olukayode Pitan, pledged the bank’s continuous support for NNFM and investments that were consistent with the current CBN Agri Initiative.</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://fmnplc.com/bank-industry-boss-visits-sorghum-mill-northern-nigeria-flour-mills-kano/">Bank Of Industry Boss Visits Sorghum Mill At Northern Nigeria Flour Mills In Kano</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://fmnplc.com">FMN</a>.</p>
