						<post-id xmlns="com-wordpress:feed-additions:1">1513</post-id>	</item>
		<item>
		<title>THE EXIT OF AN INDUSTRY ICON</title>
		<link>https://fmnplc.com/exit-industry-icon/</link>
				<comments>https://fmnplc.com/exit-industry-icon/#comments</comments>
				<pubDate>Tue, 25 Oct 2016 19:37:56 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[General]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Press]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://fmnplc.com/?p=1455</guid>
				<description><![CDATA[<p>The Chairman, Board of Directors and Management of Flour Mills of Nigeria PLC (FMN) have announced with deep regret, the death of the founding father of the Company and Chairman Emeritus, Mr. George Stavros Coumantaros. He passed on peacefully in his sleep on Monday, 17th October 2016, in Athens, Greece, at the age of 94. [&#8230;]</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://fmnplc.com/exit-industry-icon/">THE EXIT OF AN INDUSTRY ICON</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://fmnplc.com">FMN</a>.</p>
]]></description>
								<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>The Chairman, Board of Directors and Management of Flour Mills of Nigeria PLC (FMN) have announced with deep regret, the death of the founding father of the Company and Chairman Emeritus, Mr. George Stavros Coumantaros. He passed on peacefully in his sleep on Monday, 17th October 2016, in Athens, Greece, at the age of 94.</p>
<p>Mr. Coumantaros is a visionary and dynamic leader, who founded Flour Mills of Nigeria Plc in September 1960. The company pioneered flour milling in Nigeria when its first mill was commissioned in Apapa in 1962. Today, the Apapa milling complex has grown to become one of the largest single site mills in the world. Due to Mr. Coumantaros’ passion and absolute commitment to Nigeria’s economic growth and development, FMN has been positioned as the foremost food and agro- allied group in the country.</p>
<p>George Coumantaros, a rare breed, will be sorely missed by Shareholders, Directors, Management, Employees and Customers of Flour Mills of Nigeria Plc for his vision, inspiration, dynamism, forthrightness, courage and passion which laid the foundation for “The FMN Dream”.</p>
<p>The greatest tribute that Directors, Management, and Staff of the FMN can pay to Mr. George Stavros Coumantaros is to carry on with his legacy of hard work and commitment to the advancement of the Company and Nigeria’s economy.</p>
<p><strong>MR. PAUL GBEDEDO<br />
GROUP MANAGING DIRECTOR</strong></p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://fmnplc.com/exit-industry-icon/">THE EXIT OF AN INDUSTRY ICON</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://fmnplc.com">FMN</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
